The key advantage of this approach lies in its inherent scalability and fault tolerance. By leveraging the durability and availability of object storage, the distributed queue can seamlessly handle spikes in traffic and withstand infrastructure failures, ensuring uninterrupted message processing. The use of a JSON file as the underlying data structure offers a familiar and flexible format, simplifying integration and maintenance.

One of the primary challenges in building a distributed queue is ensuring consistent message delivery and processing. The solution presented in this topic addresses this by implementing a robust locking mechanism within the JSON file, allowing multiple consumers to safely dequeue messages without the risk of duplication. This approach also enables efficient message prioritization, ensuring that high-priority tasks are processed in a timely manner.

Another notable aspect of this distributed queue system is its ability to scale horizontally. As the volume of messages increases, additional consumers can be seamlessly added to the system, distributing the workload and maintaining high throughput. The use of object storage as the underlying storage layer provides virtually limitless scalability, allowing the queue to grow alongside the demands of the application.

