  "meta_description": "As Ukraine's war with Russia enters its fifth year, the country holds solemn remembrance ceremonies to honor those who have lost their lives in the conflict.",
  "summary_30w": "Ukraine marks 5 years of war with Russia, holding ceremonies to remember the thousands who have died in the ongoing conflict that has devastated the country.",
  "article": "Ukraine is marking the fifth year of its war with Russia, a conflict that has claimed thousands of lives and devastated the country. On Sunday, Ukrainians gathered across the nation to honor those who have fallen in the fighting, with solemn remembrance ceremonies and vigils held to commemorate the grim milestone.

The war in eastern Ukraine began in 2014 after Russia's annexation of Crimea and the outbreak of a Russia-backed separatist insurgency in the Donbas region. Since then, the conflict has claimed over 13,000 lives, with many more wounded and displaced from their homes.

In the capital Kyiv, President Volodymyr Zelenskyy laid flowers at a memorial to the \"Heavenly Hundred\", the protesters killed during the 2014 Maidan uprising that toppled the pro-Russian president. Zelenskyy praised the sacrifice of those who gave their lives for Ukraine's independence and territorial integrity.

\"We will never forget those who gave their lives for Ukraine,\" Zelenskyy said. \"Their memory will live on in our hearts and in the history of our nation.\"

Across the country, Ukrainians held candlelight vigils, laid flowers at war memorials, and observed moments of silence to pay tribute to the fallen. In the eastern city of Mariupol, which has been on the frontlines of the conflict, residents gathered to release balloons into the sky in memory of those killed.

The war in Ukraine has been a protracted and bloody affair, with little progress made towards a lasting peace settlement. Ceasefire agreements have frequently been violated, and the fighting has continued to rage, particularly in the Donbas region.

