  "article": "In a significant development, NASA has officially designated the recent failure of the Boeing Starliner spacecraft as a maximum-level Type A mishap, the agency's most serious classification for an incident. This designation underscores the gravity of the Starliner's malfunction, which occurred during an uncrewed test flight to the International Space Station in December 2019.

