  "article": "Conor McGregor, the former two-division UFC champion, has once again found himself at the center of a social media storm after venting his frustration over ongoing contract negotiations with the promotion.

In a now-deleted tweet, McGregor expressed his dissatisfaction with the UFC's handling of the negotiations, stating that he is \"not interested\" in the current offers on the table. The Irishman's outburst has sparked a flurry of speculation and discussion within the MMA community, with fans and analysts weighing in on the potential implications of this latest development.

McGregor's relationship with the UFC has been a complex one, marked by both success and controversy. The charismatic fighter has been a major draw for the promotion, headlining some of the biggest pay-per-view events in the organization's history. However, his outspoken nature and willingness to challenge the status quo have also led to tensions with the UFC's leadership.

The latest episode in this ongoing saga comes at a crucial time for McGregor's career. The former featherweight and lightweight champion has not competed in the UFC since his loss to Dustin Poirier in their trilogy fight in July 2021. Since then, he has been focused on his recovery from a leg injury sustained in that bout, as well as exploring other business ventures outside of the Octagon.

