\"We are excited to work with Pearl Abyss to bring the benefits of FidelityFX Super Resolution to Crimson Desert,\" said Scott Herkelman, corporate vice president and general manager of the Graphics Business Unit at AMD. \"FSR is designed to provide a significant performance boost without compromising image quality, and we believe it will be a valuable asset for Crimson Desert players across a variety of hardware setups.\"

The integration of FSR into Crimson Desert is particularly significant, as the game is set to push the boundaries of visual fidelity and performance on modern gaming hardware. By leveraging AMD's upscaling technology, developers can ensure that players with a wide range of GPU configurations can enjoy the game's stunning visuals and smooth gameplay.

\"Crimson Desert is a visually stunning game that will push the limits of what's possible on modern gaming hardware,\" said Jae-Hoon Kim, chief executive officer of Pearl Abyss. \"By incorporating AMD's FidelityFX Super Resolution, we can ensure that players of all hardware levels can experience the game's breathtaking world and intense combat sequences without sacrificing performance.\"

The announcement of Crimson Desert's support for FSR comes at a time when the technology is gaining significant traction within the gaming industry. Several high-profile titles, including Godfall, Terminator: Resistance, and Necromunda: Hired Gun, have already integrated FSR, and the list of supported games is expected to grow rapidly in the coming months.

